Pres COCHRANE, Appellant, v. S. J. HOOPER, Appellee. No. 11365. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Feb. 6, 1946. T. Harvey Hedgepeth and Raymond W. Miller, both of Jackson, Miss., for appellant. W. Calvin Wells and W. R. Newman, both of Jackson, Miss., for appellee.

Before McCORD and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment appeal from is affirmed on the authority of Hamilton v. Morrison, 5 Cir., 146 F.2d 533, and Welsh v. Williams, 85 Miss. 301, 37 So. 561.
